1.00 mL of TM standard solution at different concentrations was mixed with the Y-G-CDs. Then, the mixed solution was adjusted to pH 5.0 by adding Britton-Robinson buffer solution (BR solution, pH 2–12). The fluorescence intensity of blank Y-G-CDs was recorded as F0
                        . After 30 min of incubation at room temperature, the fluorescence intensities of Y-G-CDs were recorded at F. The fluorescence detection performance was also analyzed. All fluorescence measurements were performed using a 440 nm excitation wavelength. Measurement of a linear relationship between fluorescence intensity ratio (F/F0
                        ) values and TM concentration. All experiments are conducted with triple parallel tests to increase the reliability of the experiment.
